        <briefdescription>
<para>This table contains configuration information for each intc device in the system. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="struct_x_intc" kindref="compound">XIntc</ref> driver must know when to acknowledge the interrupt. The entry which specifies this as a bit mask where each bit corresponds to a specific interrupt. A bit set indicates to ack it before servicing it. Generally, acknowledge before service is used when the interrupt signal is edge-sensitive, and after when the signal is level-sensitive.</para><para>Refer to the <ref refid="struct_x_intc___config" kindref="compound">XIntc_Config</ref> data structure in <ref refid="xintc_8h" kindref="compound">xintc.h</ref> for details on how this table should be initialized. </para>        </detaileddescription>
